This the source code of Riemannian VLAD using the Affine Invariant Riemannian  Metric (AIRM), Stein, and Jeffrey divergences on a toy dataset.
To obtain the accuracy scores (with nearest neighbour), run the script “R_VLAD_SPD.m”.
The size of the dictionary, "K", is kept fixed to 16.

Please cite the following paper if your are using this code:
"More About VLAD: A Leap from Euclidean to Riemannian Manifolds", 
Masoud Faraki, Mehrtash Harandi, and Fatih Porikli, 
In Proc. IEEE Conference on Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition
(CVPR), Boston, USA, 2015.

